    <key>CBReleaseWhatsNew</key>
    <string>Tiny popover height now hugs its content. The visible whitespace strip that used to sit between the last account row and the Day / Week / Month token strip is gone — the account list is now wrapped in a bounded ScrollView whose height is computed exactly from row count × row height + spacing, instead of consuming every remaining pixel via maxHeight: .infinity. rowHeight was also re-measured (38pt vs the previous 46pt over-budget) and inner paddings on the token strip and auto-swap bar were tightened by a couple of points.
Tiny popover scroll cap is now 4 rows. Past 4 accounts the list scrolls inside its bounded frame; the token strip and auto-swap controls stay anchored at the bottom.
Empty-account state in Tiny now uses a fixed 90pt slot instead of letting the popover collapse arbitrarily.</string>
    <key>CBReleaseHotfixes</key>
